    "He was an editor for <em>Art International</em>, collecting art in his spare time.": [],
    "Rubin bought the new Abstract Expressionist art of Jasper Johns and Frank Stella.": [],
    "His dissertation, granted from Columbia in 1959, was on modern ecclesiastic art.": [],
    "During this time, too, Rubin strengthened his friendship with <a href=\"/barra\">Alfred H. Barr, Jr.</a>, the founder and \"Director of Collections\" at the Museum of Modern Art, inviting Barr to lecture at Sarah Lawrence.": [],
